    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, i get that people want safety, but isn't it a bit reductive to just say the stats settle it? if a law is unconstitutional, it doesn't really matter if the data says it helps, right? it feels like you're saying the data is the only thing that's actually \"real\" and the legal side is just an afterthought.",
